# Session state — local, per-machine, regenerated on each session-start.
# Ignore everything inside .harness-state/ EXCEPT triage-log.md (audit trail
# for /triage-parking, meant to persist across machines per the skill's
# always-log invariant). File-level patterns are required because gitignore
# cannot re-include a file whose parent directory is excluded.
.harness-state/*
!.harness-state/triage-log.md

# /planning-loop side-path copy — ephemeral, written/deleted by the skill.
# Pattern protects against accidental commit if a run is interrupted before
# the restore helper runs. See skills/planning-loop/SKILL.md Step 5b.
docs/specs/_REVIEW-*

# /planning-loop auto-apply temp file — written by Step 6f, consumed by the
# atomic rename at the commit point. Pattern protects against accidental
# commit if a run is interrupted between temp-write and rename. The orphan
# detector at Step 1 pre-flight reports any leftover; restore.sh deletes it.
*.autoapply-tmp

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
